<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>STEPS – FETP India Decision Aid</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">

    <!-- Chart.js -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@4.4.1/dist/chart.umd.min.js"></script>
    <!-- jsPDF -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/jspdf@2.5.1/dist/jspdf.umd.min.js"></script>
    <!-- SheetJS for Excel export -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/xlsx@0.18.5/dist/xlsx.full.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
<header class="app-header">
    <div class="app-header-left">
        <div class="app-logo-circle">S</div>
        <div class="app-title-block">
            <h1 class="app-title">STEPS – FETP India Decision Aid</h1>
            <p class="app-subtitle">Scalable Training Estimation and Planning System for FETP India</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="app-header-center">
        <div class="app-header-line">Linking DCE preferences, cohort costs and outbreak benefits.</div>
        <div class="app-header-line">Designed for workshops with Government of India, WHO, World Bank and partners.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="app-header-right">
        <span class="badge badge-soft">Version 1 draft</span>
        <button id="btn-start-tour" class="btn-ghost-small">
            <span class="tour-icon">?</span>
            <span>Quick tour</span>
        </button>
    </div>
</header>

<main class="app-shell">
    <div class="card card-secondary">
        <h2>STEPS overview</h2>
        <p>
            STEPS helps you stress test FETP scale up options by combining discrete choice experiment (DCE) preferences
            with simple cost and epidemiological calculations. Use the tabs below to configure a programme, review
            predicted endorsement and value for money, compare scenarios, and access a plain language technical appendix.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <nav class="tab-bar" aria-label="Main tabs">
            <button class="tab-link active" data-tab="intro" type="button">Introduction</button>
            <button class="tab-link" data-tab="config" type="button">Configuration</button>
            <button class="tab-link" data-tab="results" type="button">Results</button>
            <button class="tab-link" data-tab="costing" type="button">Costing</button>
            <button class="tab-link" data-tab="natsim" type="button">National simulation</button>
            <button class="tab-link" data-tab="sensitivity" type="button">DCE sensitivity &amp; CBA</button>
            <button class="tab-link" data-tab="technical" type="button">Technical settings</button>
        </nav>

        <!-- Intro tab -->
        <section id="tab-intro" class="tab-panel active">
            <div class="app-main-layout">
                <div class="app-main-column">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h2>What this tool is for</h2>
                        <p>
                            STEPS is a decision aid for discussions about strengthening and scaling FETP programmes in India.
                            It is intended for exploratory use during workshops and business case preparation. The numbers are
                            indicative and should be refined using programme budgets and updated epidemiological evidence.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The engine combines:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="plain-list">
                            <li>DCE-based endorsement of alternative FETP designs.</li>
                            <li>Programme costs per trainee per month, scaled up by cohort size and duration.</li>
                            <li>Simple epidemiological multipliers for graduates and outbreak responses.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="app-main-column">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h3>How to use STEPS in a meeting</h3>
                        <ol class="plain-list numbered">
                            <li>Go to the <strong>Configuration</strong> tab and choose tier, incentives, delivery and cohort assumptions.</li>
                            <li>Click <strong>Apply configuration</strong> to update endorsement, costs and benefits.</li>
                            <li>Use the <strong>Results</strong> and <strong>Costing</strong> tabs to explain the option.</li>
                            <li>Save interesting options into the <strong>scenario portfolio</strong> on the National simulation tab.</li>
                            <li>Use the <strong>DCE sensitivity &amp; CBA</strong> tab to check how results move under different assumptions.</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p class="note">
                            The tool is a draft and should be read together with the Technical Appendix and the accompanying
                            narrative in the project report.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Configuration tab -->
        <section id="tab-config" class="tab-panel">
            <div class="app-main-layout">
                <div class="app-main-column">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div class="card-title-row">
                            <div>
                                <h2>Configure an FETP option</h2>
                                <p class="card-subtitle">
                                    Choose tier, incentives, delivery, response time and cohort scale for this scenario.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex-row">
                                <span class="metric-label">Preference model</span>
                                <div class="pill-toggle-group">
                                    <button type="button"
                                            class="pill-toggle active"
                                            data-model="mxl">
                                        Average mixed logit
                                    </button>
                                    <button type="button"
                                            class="pill-toggle"
                                            data-model="lc2">
                                        Supportive group
                                    </button>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <form class="form-grid" onsubmit="return false;">
                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="program-tier">Programme tier</label>
                                <select id="program-tier">
                                    <option value="frontline">Frontline (3 months)</option>
                                    <option value="intermediate">Intermediate (12 months)</option>
                                    <option value="advanced">Advanced (24 months)</option>
                                </select>
                                <p class="hint">Choose the main FETP tier for this configuration.</p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="career-track">Career incentive</label>
                                <select id="career-track">
                                    <option value="certificate">Government and partner certificate</option>
                                    <option value="uniqual">University qualification</option>
                                    <option value="career_path">Government career pathway</option>
                                </select>
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="mentorship">
                                    Mentorship intensity
                                </label>
                                <select id="mentorship">
                                    <option value="low">Low mentorship</option>
                                    <option value="medium">Medium mentorship</option>
                                    <option value="high">High mentorship</option>
                                </select>
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="delivery">Delivery mode</label>
                                <select id="delivery">
                                    <option value="blended">Blended delivery</option>
                                    <option value="inperson">Fully in person delivery</option>
                                    <option value="online">Fully online delivery</option>
                                </select>
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="response">Outbreak response time</label>
                                <select id="response">
                                    <option value="30">Detect and respond within 30 days</option>
                                    <option value="15">Detect and respond within 15 days</option>
                                    <option value="7">Detect and respond within 7 days</option>
                                </select>
                                <p class="hint">Used as a multiplier on outbreak-related benefits.</p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="trainees">Trainees per cohort</label>
                                <input id="trainees" type="number" min="1" step="1" value="25">
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="cohorts">Number of cohorts</label>
                                <input id="cohorts" type="number" min="1" step="1" value="6">
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group form-group-wide">
                                <label for="cost-slider">
                                    Cost per trainee per month
                                </label>
                                <input id="cost-slider" type="range" min="5000" max="60000" step="1000" value="20000">
                                <div class="slider-value">
                                    <span class="metric-label">Indicative programme cost per trainee per month</span>
                                    <span id="cost-display" class="metric-value">INR 20,000</span>
                                </div>
                                <p class="hint">
                                    Use this to align the modelled cost with your draft budget. Cost templates in the
                                    Costing tab provide a breakdown.
                                </p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group form-group-wide">
                                <label>
                                    Opportunity cost of trainee time
                                </label>
                                <button type="button" id="opp-toggle" class="switch-pill on">
                                    <div class="switch-knob"></div>
                                    <span class="switch-label">Opportunity cost included</span>
                                </button>
                                <p class="hint">
                                    When included, the tool adds an opportunity cost percentage on top of direct
                                    programme costs using the selected template.
                                </p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="scenario-name">Scenario label (optional)</label>
                                <input id="scenario-name"
                                       type="text"
                                       placeholder="e.g. Advanced, high mentorship, 6 cohorts">
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group form-group-wide">
                                <label for="scenario-notes">Short notes (optional)</label>
                                <textarea id="scenario-notes" rows="2"
                                          placeholder="Add a reminder about key assumptions or intended use."></textarea>
                            </div>
                        </form>

                        <div class="button-row button-row-main">
                            <button id="update-results" class="btn-primary" type="button">
                                Apply configuration
                            </button>
                            <button id="open-snapshot" class="btn-secondary" type="button">
                                Open snapshot
                            </button>
                            <button id="save-scenario" class="btn-ghost" type="button">
                                Save to portfolio
                            </button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="app-main-column">
                    <div class="card config-summary-card">
                        <div class="config-summary-header">
                            <div>
                                <h2>Summary and recommendation</h2>
                                <p class="card-subtitle">
                                    Interprets DCE endorsement, costs and benefits for this configuration.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="metric-block">
                                <div class="metric-label">Predicted endorsement</div>
                                <div id="config-endorsement-value" class="metric-value">–</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="flex-between" style="margin-bottom:8px;">
                            <div class="headline-status">
                                <span id="headline-status-pill"
                                      class="status-pill status-neutral">
                                    Scenario not yet classified
                                </span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex-row">
                                <span class="metric-label">Display currency</span>
                                <div class="pill-toggle-group">
                                    <button type="button"
                                            class="pill-toggle active"
                                            data-currency="INR">
                                        INR
                                    </button>
                                    <button type="button"
                                            class="pill-toggle"
                                            data-currency="USD">
                                        USD
                                    </button>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="headline-recommendation" class="headline-text">
                            Apply a configuration to see an interpreted recommendation based on endorsement and benefit
                            cost ratio.
                        </div>

                        <div class="headline-briefing">
                            <h4>Briefing note</h4>
                            <p id="headline-briefing-text" class="text-muted">
                                Once you apply a configuration, this section summarises endorsement, costs, indicative
                                benefits and epidemiological outputs in plain language for use in concept notes and
                                business case documents.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <hr class="divider">

                        <div id="config-summary" class="config-summary"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Results tab -->
        <section id="tab-results" class="tab-panel">
            <div class="app-main-layout">
                <div class="app-main-column">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h2>Endorsement and opt out</h2>
                        <p class="card-subtitle">
                            Shares of stakeholders predicted to endorse the FETP option versus opting out.
                        </p>
                        <div class="kpi-grid">
                            <div class="kpi-card">
                                <div class="kpi-label">Endorse FETP option</div>
                                <div id="endorsement-rate" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                                <div class="kpi-small-note">Derived from the selected DCE model.</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="kpi-card">
                                <div class="kpi-label">Choose opt out</div>
                                <div id="optout-rate" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                                <div class="kpi-small-note">Stakeholders preferring no investment under this design.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="chart-block">
                            <canvas id="chart-uptake" aria-label="Endorsement and opt out chart"></canvas>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card">
                        <h3>Epidemiological outputs</h3>
                        <p class="card-subtitle">
                            Graduates and outbreak responses implied by the current configuration and planning horizon.
                        </p>
                        <div class="kpi-grid">
                            <div class="kpi-card">
                                <div class="kpi-label">Total FETP graduates</div>
                                <div id="epi-graduates" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="kpi-card">
                                <div class="kpi-label">Outbreak responses per year</div>
                                <div id="epi-outbreaks" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="kpi-card">
                                <div class="kpi-label">Indicative benefit per cohort</div>
                                <div id="epi-benefit" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="chart-block">
                            <canvas id="chart-epi" aria-label="Epidemiological outputs chart"></canvas>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="app-main-column">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h2>Economic value per cohort</h2>
                        <p class="card-subtitle">
                            Economic costs and indicative benefits per cohort for the current configuration.
                        </p>
                        <div class="kpi-grid">
                            <div class="kpi-card">
                                <div class="kpi-label">Economic cost per cohort</div>
                                <div id="total-cost" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="kpi-card">
                                <div class="kpi-label">Net benefit per cohort</div>
                                <div id="net-benefit" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="kpi-card">
                                <div class="kpi-label">Benefit cost ratio</div>
                                <div id="bcr" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="metric-single">
                            <div class="metric-label">Willingness to pay (per trainee per month)</div>
                            <div id="wtp-config" class="metric-value">–</div>
                            <p class="metric-caption">
                                Model-based willingness to pay for moving from the baseline configuration to this design.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="chart-block">
                            <canvas id="chart-bcr" aria-label="Cost and benefit per cohort chart"></canvas>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Costing tab -->
        <section id="tab-costing" class="tab-panel">
            <div class="app-main-layout">
                <div class="app-main-column">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h2>Cost template and settings</h2>
                        <p class="card-subtitle">
                            Choose a costing template for this tier. Templates reflect different budgeting sources.
                        </p>
                        <div class="form-grid">
                            <div class="form-group form-group-wide">
                                <label for="cost-source">
                                    Cost template
                                    <button class="info-icon"
                                            type="button"
                                            title="Templates provide indicative shares for staff, travel, materials, supervision and overheads.">
                                        i
                                    </button>
                                </label>
                                <select id="cost-source">
                                    <option>Loading templates…</option>
                                </select>
                                <p id="cost-template-description" class="hint"></p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <p class="note">
                            You can override these assumptions by editing <code>cost_config.json</code> in the same
                            folder as this tool. When present, that file takes precedence over the built-in templates.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="app-main-column">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h2>Cost breakdown per cohort</h2>
                        <div id="cost-breakdown-summary" class="cost-summary"></div>

                        <div class="table-wrapper">
                            <table class="data-table">
                                <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Cost component</th>
                                    <th>Share of direct cost</th>
                                    <th>Amount per cohort</th>
                                    <th>Amount per trainee per month</th>
                                    <th>Notes</th>
                                </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody id="cost-components-list"></tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- National simulation tab -->
        <section id="tab-natsim" class="tab-panel">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-title-row">
                    <div>
                        <h2>National simulation and scenario portfolio</h2>
                        <p class="card-subtitle">
                            Scale results across cohorts and compare multiple saved scenarios side by side.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="export-toolbar">
                        <button id="export-excel" class="btn-secondary" type="button">
                            Export scenarios to Excel
                        </button>
                        <button id="export-pdf" class="btn-ghost" type="button">
                            Export current policy brief (PDF)
                        </button>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="kpi-grid">
                    <div class="kpi-card">
                        <div class="kpi-label">Total economic cost (all cohorts)</div>
                        <div id="nat-total-cost" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="kpi-card">
                        <div class="kpi-label">Total indicative benefit (all cohorts)</div>
                        <div id="nat-total-benefit" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="kpi-card">
                        <div class="kpi-label">Net benefit (all cohorts)</div>
                        <div id="nat-net-benefit" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="kpi-card">
                        <div class="kpi-label">Benefit cost ratio</div>
                        <div id="nat-bcr" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="kpi-card">
                        <div class="kpi-label">Total graduates</div>
                        <div id="nat-graduates" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="kpi-card">
                        <div class="kpi-label">Outbreak responses per year</div>
                        <div id="nat-outbreaks" class="kpi-value">–</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="grid-two-stretch" style="margin-top:12px;">
                    <div class="natsim-column">
                        <h3>Costs and benefits across scenarios</h3>
                        <div class="chart-block">
                            <canvas id="chart-nat-cost-benefit"
                                    aria-label="Costs and benefits across scenarios"></canvas>
                        </div>
                        <div class="chart-block">
                            <canvas id="chart-nat-bcr"
                                    aria-label="Benefit cost ratios across scenarios"></canvas>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="natsim-column">
                        <h3>Graduates and outbreak responses</h3>
                        <div class="chart-block">
                            <canvas id="chart-nat-grad-outbreak"
                                    aria-label="Graduates and outbreak responses across scenarios"></canvas>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="divider">

                <h3>Saved scenario portfolio</h3>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    Use <strong>Save to portfolio</strong> on the Configuration tab to add or update rows in this table.
                </p>
                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <table id="scenario-table" class="data-table">
                        <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Scenario</th>
                            <th>Programme tier</th>
                            <th>Mentorship</th>
                            <th>Response time</th>
                            <th>Number of cohorts</th>
                            <th>Trainees per cohort</th>
                            <th>Cost per trainee per month</th>
                            <th>Preference model</th>
                            <th>Endorsement</th>
                            <th>BCR</th>
                            <th>Net benefit (all cohorts)</th>
                        </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody></tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- DCE sensitivity & CBA tab -->
        <section id="tab-sensitivity" class="tab-panel">
            <div class="app-main-layout">
                <div class="app-main-column">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h2>DCE benefits and sensitivity analysis</h2>
                        <p class="card-subtitle">
                            Adjust endorsement and benefit multipliers to see how DCE-based benefit cost ratios respond.
                        </p>

                        <div class="form-grid">
                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="sens-endorsement-rate">
                                    Endorsement rate override
                                    <button class="info-icon" type="button"
                                            title="Enter a value like 70 for 70 percent or 0.7 for 70 percent. Leave blank to use the model-based endorsement.">
                                        i
                                    </button>
                                </label>
                                <input id="sens-endorsement-rate"
                                       type="number"
                                       min="0"
                                       step="0.1"
                                       placeholder="Use model baseline">
                                <p class="hint">Optional; applies to DCE sensitivity only.</p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="sens-dce-benefit-scale">
                                    DCE benefit scale (%)
                                </label>
                                <input id="sens-dce-benefit-scale"
                                       type="number"
                                       min="10"
                                       max="300"
                                       step="5"
                                       value="100">
                                <p class="hint">100 keeps DCE benefits as estimated; 80 reduces them by 20 percent.</p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="sens-epi-benefit-scale">
                                    Outbreak benefit scale (%)
                                </label>
                                <input id="sens-epi-benefit-scale"
                                       type="number"
                                       min="0"
                                       max="300"
                                       step="5"
                                       value="100">
                                <p class="hint">Scales outbreak-related benefits used in the combined BCR.</p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label>
                                    Include outbreak benefits in combined BCR
                                </label>
                                <div class="flex-row">
                                    <input id="dce-epi-benefit-toggle"
                                           type="checkbox"
                                           checked
                                           style="width:auto; margin-right:4px;">
                                    <span class="hint">Untick to show DCE benefit only.</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="headline-briefing" style="margin-top:12px;">
                            <h4>Share of benefit from outbreak response</h4>
                            <p id="dce-response-share-label" class="text-muted">
                                Once a configuration is applied, this line will show how much of the overall DCE-based
                                benefit is driven by faster outbreak response capacity.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="app-main-column">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h3>DCE CBA profiles</h3>
                        <p class="card-subtitle">
                            Results are reported separately for the overall mixed logit and the supportive latent class.
                        </p>
                        <div class="table-wrapper">
                            <table id="dce-sensitivity-table" class="data-table">
                                <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Model / group</th>
                                    <th>Total cost (all cohorts)</th>
                                    <th>DCE benefit (all cohorts)</th>
                                    <th>Outbreak-response component</th>
                                    <th>Outbreak benefits (all cohorts)</th>
                                    <th>BCR (DCE only)</th>
                                    <th>NPV (DCE only)</th>
                                    <th>BCR (DCE + outbreak)</th>
                                    <th>NPV (DCE + outbreak)</th>
                                    <th>BCR (endorsers only)</th>
                                    <th>NPV (endorsers only)</th>
                                </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody></tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>

                        <div id="dce-sensitivity-summary" class="kpi-grid" style="margin-top:10px;"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Technical tab -->
        <section id="tab-technical" class="tab-panel">
            <div class="grid-two-stretch">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2>Advanced epidemiological settings</h2>
                    <p class="card-subtitle">
                        Adjust default multipliers when working with subject matter experts. Values apply across all
                        configurations.
                    </p>

                    <div class="form-grid">
                        <div class="form-group form-group-wide">
                            <label for="adv-inr-per-usd">Exchange rate (INR per USD)</label>
                            <input id="adv-inr-per-usd" type="number" step="0.1" min="1">
                        </div>

                        <div class="form-group form-group-wide">
                            <h3>Frontline tier</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-group">
